resources.string: Congrats!!!! you are soon going to have a baby… \nA simple fitness plan for women in their first trimester. Always, check with your healthcare provider before starting this or any other exercise program, and STOP if anything is painful.
Baby is growing so is the need for 100% fit mommy…… stay fit and awesome for fit baby. But don’t take much pain.

Baby wants mommy to be happy and fit…… workout at your own pace and don\'t over exert yourself. Do this workout daily. Here are workout dos and don\'ts while pregnant: Stay in Shape, Tone those Muscles and Feel Fantastic.
want to stay fit mommy then keep up the spirit and keep exercising……. Follow these exercises as demonstrated.

Working out during the second trimester of pregnancy generally feels great! After battling nausea and fatigue during the first trimester, most women feel a surge of energy. As always, make sure you consult your obstetrician before you engage in any physical activity.

Keeping in good shape while you’re pregnant is one of the best things you can do for yourself and your baby. The other is to eat a healthy diet, but you knew that already! Exercise will help you gain an appropriate amount of weight without putting on too much, and it will get you ready for the rigors of birth. It can also help you feel better and sleep better.
your baby is out into this world. Your exercise should not stop but continue even as your bump grows bigger and bigger.
